From: Nickel Browser Team <team@nickel-browser.org>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 06/10] nickel: adblock-engine — source-level ad & tracker blocking

Add Nickel's ad-blocking engine as a new component under
chrome/browser/nickel/adblock/.

Architecture:
  - NickelAdBlockEngine   — core filter-list engine (Adblock Plus filter syntax)
  - NickelAdBlockService  — browser-process singleton, owns the engine
  - NickelAdBlockURLLoader — intercepts URLLoaderFactory requests in the renderer

The engine uses a compact bitset + domain tree to evaluate filter rules at
network-request time, before any bytes hit the network.  This is the same
approach used by Brave's ad-blocking (adblock-rust) and uBlock Origin.

For Chromium 146 the intercept point is
  chrome/browser/net/profile_network_context_service.cc
where NickelAdBlockURLLoaderThrottle is registered.

Filter lists ship as a compressed binary in the resources.pak; the engine
can also hot-update lists from a Nickel-maintained CDN without a full
browser update.
